# Perplexity MCP Example (Docker)

This folder contains an example of using the Model Context Protocol (MCP) with Perplexity, running entirely via Docker. You do **not** need Node.js or any other programming environmentâ€”just Docker and an MCP-compatible client!

## Prerequisites

- [Docker](https://www.docker.com/get-started) installed and running
- An MCP-compatible client or tool (see [modelcontextprotocol.io](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/introduction) for options)
- A Perplexity API key ([get one here](https://www.perplexity.ai/account/details))
